This implementation is more efficient than the previous one because it avoids storing the entire contents of the text files in memory at once, and uses textscan to parse them line by line. However, if the text files are too large to fit into memory, you may need to consider using external storage methods such as HDF5 or Parquet, or stream processing techniques to process the texts in smaller chunks. In these cases, you may also want to look into distributed computing frameworks like Apache Spark or Dask to parallelize the computation across multiple nodes.

